T1	Participants 423 485	women undergoing detoxification for heroin dependence in China
T2	Participants 540 706	Seventy-five women aged 20-37 years undergoing detoxification for heroin dependence at AnKang Hospital were allocated randomly into an intervention or a control group
T3	Participants 708 881	Women in the intervention group received a 6-month yoga intervention in addition to hospital routine care, and women in the control group received hospital routine care only
T4	Participants 1201 1277	Most female heroin addicts were young and single, with a low education level
T5	Participants 1279 1379	Most had used heroin by injection. Mood state and quality of life of female heroin addicts were poor
